<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Sim_Career_Detective" s="114793">
  <T n="category">114773<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_Get_to_Work--></T>
  <T n="name">0x365944B<!--String: "Detective Career"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP01\UI\Icons\Tutorial\Client\GetToWork\Detective_Career_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b361429596f61edf</T>
      <T n="text">0x1B46F4D3<!--String: "Is your Sim a super-sleuth? Or have a knack for catching Sims in a lie? Or perhaps just an honest-to-goodness do-gooder? Then join the ranks of Sim's finest by becoming a detective!\n\nDetectives aren’t pencil pushers stuck behind a desk - they have different locations they frequently work in: Police Station, at Crime Scenes, and they can be found patrolling the streets."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP01\UI\Icons\Tutorial\Client\GetToWork\Detective_Career_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b361429596f61edc</T>
      <T n="text">0x9EF1FE4C<!--String: "The Police Station is the main hub for police and detective activity. There are holding cells for detaining the accused, booking areas to process suspects, and interrogation rooms to...get a confession. There is also a crime lab which is used to gather and analyze clues. And of course, the office area where Sims push paperwork."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP01\UI\Icons\Tutorial\Client\GetToWork\Detective_Career_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b361429596f61edd</T>
      <T n="text">0x63955280<!--String: "Sims in the detective career will have cases assigned to them. Once a case is in hand, the Sim's job is to find and analyze clues that help point to a suspect.\n\nOnce enough clues are found, the detective can issue an APB (from the Crime Map) and start asking around to see if anyone recognizes the suspect's profile. An arrest can be made if an appropriate Sim is located."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP01\UI\Icons\Tutorial\Client\GetToWork\Detective_Career_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b361429596f61eda</T>
      <T n="text">0x84BAA942<!--String: "The more clues the detective finds, the more specific the description of the suspect. Finding more clues will also assist detectives during interrogations."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP01\UI\Icons\Tutorial\Client\GetToWork\Detective_Career_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b361429596f61edb</T>
      <T n="text">0x3F744F7F<!--String: "When on-the-job with an active case, detectives can Travel to Crime Scenes to examine the scene of the crime, search for clues, and interview witnesses. Find Travel to Crime Scene on the Crime Map, Police Desk, and when traveling to other regions in the open street."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP01\UI\Icons\Tutorial\Client\GetToWork\Detective_Career_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:b361429596f61ed8</T>
      <T n="text">0xAF367301<!--String: "Sims of the law will also patrol the streets on foot. While on patrol, officers can issue citations for littering or fighting, or get to know citizens.\n\nThe Go On Patrol interaction can be found on the Police Desk, Crime Map, and when clicking in a "travel region" in the open street."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
